item.title: About
item.description: Are you an intermediate or advanced R user looking for an opportunity to expand your knowledge and connect with the diverse R community in the Twin Cities? We’d love for you to join us VIRTUALLY at noRth 2021! noRth 2021 is coming on September 29-30, 2021. Details will be posted as available. While you wait, watch the 2020 conference or download speaker materials in the noRth Github repo. Join the Twin Cities R community today via R Ladies - Twin Cities or the Twin Cities R User Group.

item.title: Institute for Research in Statistics and its Applications
Code of Conduct
item.description: While we are virtual, we are still committed to providing a harassment-free experience for participants at our event(s). noRth is a conference intended for professional networking and collaboration in the R community. We encourage the open exchange of ideas and expression and thus require an environment that recognizes the inherent worth of every person and group. A Code of Conduct is useful to define accepted and acceptable behaviors and to promote high standards of professional practice.
